dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c Karthik b Mohammed Shami 93 (106b 9x4 0x6 181m) SR: 87.73

dismissalComment.html: nudges it straight to the keeper. But he's reviewed it. Bat was close to pad and possibly connected with the pad at the same time as he got this edge. Because there's no real reason to review this otherwise. It's at a length, just outside off. Thick edge straight to the keeper as he tried to guide it down to third man. New Zealand lose their review. Falls short of the hunded by seven runs, and now NZ have 29 balls with Bracewell and the tail.

dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham c Rayudu b Chahal 51 (64b 1x4 1x6 95m) SR: 79.68

dismissalComment.html: flicked straight to deep midwicket. Latham might have had the wind against him, but in any case, that wasn't wide enough of Rayudu to make him work for it. It's lobbed up slow on leg stump. He steps out and clips uppishly but can't get his wrists around this aggressively enough. Lobs up, stops a little as it climbs, and lands in Rayudu's hands some ten yards inside

dismissalText.commentary: Doug Bracewell run out (Kohli) 15 (18b 1x4 0x6 34m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: oh dear. Poor judgement from Bracewell. Short of a length ball at off stump. Boult with the legs scattered as he tries to stab into the off side. Gets it into the leg side off the inside edge. To Kohli's left at short midwicket. Bracewell runs down blindly. Kohli has a walk and takes off the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Trent Boult c Mohammed Shami b Kumar 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: taken by short third just behind the keeper. Slower ball at a length outside off. Walks into the leg side and heaves from under it. Slices it high and DK gets out of the way for Shami to stride across to his left. Once again, New Zealand don't bat out their overs

headshotImage.caption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma st Latham b Santner 62 (77b 3x4 2x6 115m) SR: 80.51

dismissalComment.html: oh beautiful! Lovely loopy length ball outside off. 74kph, short of a length outside off. It's how you get the big slogger in the Under-13s. Rohit obviously a much better batsman than that, but this is an ungainly heave from him. Steps out early, doesn't get anywhere near it and swings all across it. It turns away, wide outside off. Latham completes the job

headshotImage.caption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Henry Nicholls player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Nicholls b Boult 60 (74b 6x4 1x6 94m) SR: 81.08

dismissalComment.html: nicely snapped by Nicholls! Another no-feet drive from Kohli at a length ball. Length ball pushed across him. Reaches out with his hands to try and get this over extra cover on the up. Nicholls times the jump perfectly as he holds on. That was coming down too as he took it behind his head, which suggests it could have been an offcutter from Boult. He was brought back for the wicket, and he gets it
length outside off, bit of away movement, Dhawan feels for it without moving his feet and offers a simple catch to Ross Taylor at first slip

commentTextItems.html: short ball, too high and over the keeper for five wides. An underwhelming finish to what has been an underwhelming series, thoroughly dominated by India, and sealed three-nil with two matches to go

commentPostTextItems.html: That's it from Varun and me. Thanks for joining us and see you soon

Kohli: Amazing, three clinical games from us, relentlessness of the side pleasing. Haven't had a break for a while, hectic Australia tour and now this. We are three-nil up so I can relax a little. Some outstanding talent coming through. Saw Shubman batting in the nets, I wasn't even 10 percent of that at 19.

Williamson: They are teaching us a lesson and we are required to rise up to the challenge. There were small improvements today but we need more. Wasn't easy to get momentum on this wicket, Ross was brilliant. With the ball, we are going okay but we need early wickets.
Mohammed Shami is the Player of the Match: difficult to bowl against the wind, but somebody has to do the job, it's part of the game.

10.23pm No middle over jitters, no last over finishes, that was as comprehensive as it gets from India as they win a series in New Zealand after ten years. They have gotten better and better since the loss to Australia in the first ODI at Sydney and have thumped New Zealand in three anti-climactic ODIs. As is their wont, two from the top order, Rohit and Kohli today, set it up nicely and Rayudu, who had looked badly out of touch before the last ODI, batted with freedom, as did Dinesh Karthik, included instead of an injured Dhoni today. This makes it three series wins for India outside Asia in the last one year, starting with the hammering of South Africa, a closer series against Australia and another comfortable win here. England was the only place they couldn't conquer, but they'd be happy to change that at the World Cup.

dismissalComment.html: oh beautiful! Lovely loopy length ball outside off. 74kph, short of a length outside off. It's how you get the big slogger in the Under-13s. Rohit obviously a much better batsman than that, but this is an ungainly heave from him. Steps out early, doesn't get anywhere near it and swings all across it. It turns away, wide outside off. Latham completes the job

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Nicholls b Boult 60 (74b 6x4 1x6 94m) SR: 81.08

dismissalComment.html: nicely snapped by Nicholls! Another no-feet drive from Kohli at a length ball. Length ball pushed across him. Reaches out with his hands to try and get this over extra cover on the up. Nicholls times the jump perfectly as he holds on. That was coming down too as he took it behind his head, which suggests it could have been an offcutter from Boult. He was brought back for the wicket, and he gets it
